Available Tools: escalate_ticket | transfer_to_specialist | get_escalation_status | set_sla
Call Schema: { "func_call": "string", "ticket_id": "string", "reason": "string", "target_team": "string" }
Response Schema: { "ticket_id": "string", "escalated_to": "string", "reason": "string", "sla_hours": number, "status": "string" }
---
Question: Assign a 4-hour SLA to ticket TKT-2045 concerning the warehouse inventory sync failure and route it to the Logistics IT team.
Call: { "func_call": "set_sla", "ticket_id": "TKT-2045", "reason": "Warehouse inventory sync failure causing stock discrepancies", "target_team": "Logistics IT" }
Response: { "ticket_id": "TKT-2045", "escalated_to": "Logistics IT", "reason": "Warehouse inventory sync failure causing stock discrepancies", "sla_hours": 4, "status": "SLA_ACTIVE" }

Question: Verify the escalation progress for ticket TKT-3198 handled by the Cloud Architecture team to ensure the migration rollback is on schedule.
Call: { "func_call": "get_escalation_status", "ticket_id": "TKT-3198", "reason": "Verification of cloud migration rollback schedule", "target_team": "Cloud Architecture" }
Response: { "ticket_id": "TKT-3198", "escalated_to": "Cloud Architecture", "reason": "Verification of cloud migration rollback schedule", "sla_hours": 6, "status": "ON_TRACK" }

